description: Notifies the result of the provisioning engine execution.

parameters.name: WorkflowToken
parameters.description: The encrypted contents of the provisioning engine execution payload that Service Catalog sends after the Terraform product provisioning workflow starts.

parameters.name: Status
parameters.description: The status of the provisioning engine execution.

parameters.name: ResourceIdentifier
parameters.description: The ID for the provisioned product resources that are part of a resource group. UniqueTag (dict) --- The unique key-value pair for a tag that identifies provisioned product resources. Key (string) --- A unique key that's attached to a resource. Value (string) --- A unique value that's attached to a resource.

nested_params.name: UniqueTag
nested_params.description: The unique key-value pair for a tag that identifies provisioned product resources.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: A unique key that's attached to a resource.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: A unique value that's attached to a resource.

parameters.name: Outputs
parameters.description: The output of the provisioning engine execution. (dict) --- The output for the product created as the result of a request. For example, the output for a CloudFormation-backed product that creates an S3 bucket would include the S3 bucket URL. OutputKey (string) --- The output key. OutputValue (string) --- The output value. Description (string) --- The description of the output.

parameters.name: IdempotencyToken
parameters.description: The idempotency token that identifies the provisioning engine execution. This field is autopopulated if not provided.
